<br>
Goanad <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udarshuluche.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DarshuLuche</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/16/02 1:38:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=681.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Caster Balance Changes</span><hr size=1> Well, as detailed in the latest letter from Verant, some sweeping changes are about to be implemented, which I'm sure everyone already has heard about, but which has yet to be added to this thread. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Here're the caster-specific changes.<br>
<br>
No more staring at the spellbook to meditate. Ever. Again.<br>
<br>
Summon corpse line to be extended to lower levels or made easier to use (?) for necros and shadowknights.<br>
<br>
Caster focus items coming Real Soon Now (tm).<br>
<br>
Good riddance to the grouping requirement for Translocates.<br>
<br>
The necro spells Levant and Skin of the Shadow will have their nighttime restriction removed.<br>
<br>
Boy, lately it's been like Christmas every day. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grimicon.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>(Title left blank)</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/16/02 9:10:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=681.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> additional updates from test server</span><hr size=1> - Marzin's Mark now stacks with Prot of the Glades, just like Sym of Marzin.<br>
<br>
- Spell memorization speed should now take +Meditate% skill items into account<br>
<br>
- Bard song memorization time should now be faster and is affected by attributes<br>
<br>
- Scribble Notes should reduce memorization times to an even greater extent than it did before<br>
<br>
- Sense spells should now work on horseback<br>
<br>
- Divine Stun is now an activateable skill. It should have a chance to stun up to and including level 60 NPC's, though it is still resistable<br>
<br>
- We've made some changes to the code for Mesmerization and Stun. Please be aware of any anomalies. For example: Are things that are normally immune to stun or mez still immune? Are normal stun or mez spells working normally? Are spell interruptions working normally? The changes we've made shouldn't have affected the way things work, so let us know if they did<br>
<br>
